Package: string2path
Title: Rendering Font into 'data.frame'
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Hiroaki", family = "Yutani", role =
        c("aut", "cre"), email = "yutani.ini@gmail.com", comment =
        c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3385-7233")), person(given = "The authors
        of the dependency Rust crates", role = c("ctb"), comment = "see
        inst/AUTHORS file for details"))
Description: Extract glyph information from font data, and translate
        the outline curves to flattened paths or tessellated polygons.
        The converted data is returned as a 'data.frame' in
        easy-to-plot format.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 4.2)
Imports: tibble, cli
